# npm publish + CI — known failures

> **Release checklist (version + tag + publish):** see `release-version-publish.mdc`.
> **Policy:** npm publish is **CI-only** — local `pnpm publish` is blocked by `scripts/assert-ci-publish.mjs`.

## Local publish blocked (expected)

**Symptom:**

```
npm publish is CI-only for @br-validators/*.
Push a version tag on main (vX.Y.Z) or re-run .github/workflows/release.yml via workflow_dispatch.
```

**Fix:** Do not use `npm login` for releases. Push tag or re-run the Release workflow.

## Release CI: tag vs package.json mismatch

**Symptom:**

```
Tag version 0.11.0-alpha.1 does not match package.json (core=0.11.0-alpha.0, cli=0.11.0-alpha.0)
```

**Cause:** Git tag pushed **before** bumping all six publishable `package.json` files.

**Fix:**

1. Bump all six `package.json` to the target version; update `CHANGELOG`; merge to `main`.
2. Delete erroneous tag: `git push origin :refs/tags/vX.Y.Z`
3. Tag `main` HEAD: `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z" && git push origin vX.Y.Z`

**Prevent:** run pre-tag check in `release-version-publish.mdc`.

## npm `401` in GitHub Actions Release workflow

**Cause:** Missing or invalid `NPM_TOKEN` secret; or granular token without write/create on `@br-validators/*`.

**Fix:** GitHub → Settings → Secrets → `NPM_TOKEN`. Use Automation token or granular token with read/write on **all** `@br-validators/*` (include **create new packages**). Re-run Release workflow.

## npm `401` locally (`npm whoami`)

**Cause:** Not logged in — irrelevant for releases (CI-only).

**Fix:** Use tag push or workflow_dispatch — do not publish locally.

## CI: parallel `pretypecheck` kills `@br-validators/core` build

**Symptom:**

```
packages/br-validators-zod pretypecheck: ERR_PNPM_RECURSIVE_RUN_FIRST_FAIL @br-validators/core build: tsup Exit status 1
```

**Cause:** `pnpm -r typecheck` runs **in parallel**; multiple packages' `pretypecheck` each run `tsup`, which **cleans `dist/`** concurrently → race.

**Fix:** Root `package.json` MUST use sequential recursive typecheck:

```json
"typecheck": "pnpm --filter @br-validators/core build && pnpm -r --sequential typecheck"
```

CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) MUST build core **once** before `pnpm typecheck`.

## Release order (this repo)

1. `pnpm verify` green on `developing`
2. PR `developing` → `main` (CI + maintainer approval)
3. Version bump + `CHANGELOG` + **npm README audit** (see `release-version-publish.mdc`) on `main`
4. `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z` → **Release workflow** publishes all six npm packages + GitHub Release
5. Sync `developing` from `main`

GitHub secret required: **`NPM_TOKEN`** (Automation or granular, all `@br-validators/*`) — see `docs/BRANCHING.md`.

## CI Release workflow: `NPM_TOKEN` missing or `express`/`vue` not created

**Symptom:** Release job fails at publish with `401` / `ENEEDAUTH`, or `express`/`vue` never appear on npm.

**Fix:** Update `NPM_TOKEN` with create + publish on entire `@br-validators` scope. Re-run workflow (idempotent — skips versions already published).

## Release CI: data tag must match npm SemVer (`1.8.3-data.1`, not `1.8.3-data.0001`)

**Symptom:**

```
Expected @br-validators/core@1.8.3-data.0001, got: 1.8.3-data.1
```

**Cause:** Zero-padded prerelease counters (`-data.0001`) are normalized by npm to `-data.1`. Tags and `package.json` must use the **same** string npm stores.

**Fix:** `scripts/lib/bump-data-version.ts` emits `1.8.3-data.1` (no leading zeroes). Re-tag failed releases as `v1.8.3-data.1` and re-run Release workflow (publish skips if already on npm).
